<subSubSection id="C34065156322FFD8FF12FEF5FD97FCFB" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6322FFD8FF12FEF5FECBFDF7" blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FF12FEF5FE8AFEF3" bold="true" box="[151,269,259,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Remarks:</emphasis>
This specimen was received from Genoa in 1888 and is indicated as 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FB86FEF5FBD1FEF3" box="[1027,1110,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">‘tipico’</emphasis>
in the accompanying list (see discussion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6322FFD8FEB7FED1FDD0FEAF" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[306,599,295,321]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FEB7FED1FDD0FEAF" box="[306,599,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Melanocharis chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above). The original label is not present, only a replacement label that has been added at NHMO (
<figureCitation id="13612A1B6322FFD8FE24FEBDFD95FE88" box="[417,530,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,787,811]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,186,761]" captionTargetId="figure-24@16.[149,1437,181,763]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by T. Salvadori. a) Ptilotis erythropleura NHMO-BI-86778 (collector’s label); b) Melanocharis chloroptera NHMO-BI-61863 (NHMO label); c) Zosterops novae guineae NHMO-BI-86649 (NHMO label); d) Dicaeum misoriense NHMO-BI-61856 (collector’s label)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626777/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Figure 6c</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FDA2FEBDFD62FE8B" author="Salvadori, T." box="[551,741,331,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="317 - 347" refId="ref16359" refString="Salvadori, T. (1878) Descrizione di trentuna specie nuove di uccelli della sottoregione papuana, e note intorno ad altre poco conosciute. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 12, 317 - 347." type="journal article" year="1878">Salvadori (1878)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify an exact number of specimens in his original publication, but in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FEEEFE99FDACFE67" author="Salvadori, T." box="[363,555,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, he listed 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176322FFD8FD19FE99FCD7FE67" box="[668,848,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
(
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FCE5FE99FC0CFE67" box="[864,907,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">a–h</emphasis>
) as 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6322FFD8FC3CFE99FC73FE67" box="[953,1012,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">types</typeStatus>
of the species. Based on the information available on the current label, the NHMO specimen corresponds to specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FBB0FE65FBC4FE43" box="[1077,1091,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">b</emphasis>
. Salvadori spelled the specific epithet in two words, 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FE02FE41FDBCFE3F" box="[391,571,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6322FFD8FE0EFE41FE54FE3F" box="[395,467,439,465]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="novae">novae</taxonomicName>
guineae’
</emphasis>
, in both of the mentioned publications, but in accordance with article 32.5.2.2 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FEACFE2DFC5EFE1B" author="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[297,985,475,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref14975" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999</bibRefCitation>
) it has later been changed to the current 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FF12FE09FEC2FDF7" box="[151,325,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">‘novaeguineae’</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6322FFD8FF42FDD5FE1CFD6B" blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
Three other 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6322FFD8FED5FDD5FE35FDD3" box="[336,434,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">syntypes</typeStatus>
are in MSNG (C.E. 11526–11528; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FCBBFDD5FBA6FDD3" author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[830,1057,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FC23FDD5FC59FDD3" box="[934,990,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">et al.</emphasis>
1979
</bibRefCitation>
), corresponding to specimens 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FAF1FDD5FA07FDD2" box="[1396,1408,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">e</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FA0BFDD5FA1BFDD2" box="[1422,1436,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">g</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FF42FDB1FF52FD8F" box="[199,213,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">h</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FF7FFDB1FE3DFD8F" author="Salvadori, T." box="[250,442,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, and in MRSN specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FD5FFDB1FD6FFD8E" box="[730,744,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">a</emphasis>
is registered as MZUT Av4174 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FBDFFDB1FABDFD8F" author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[1114,1338,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6322FFD8FB3AFDB1FB70FD8F" box="[1215,1271,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
; Giorgio Aimassi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6322FFD8FF42FD79FD97FCFB" blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
A fifth specimen is in RMNH (RMNH 90782, collected by Bruijn in Arfak, 
<date id="FFE4105E6322FFD8FB80FD79FB3AFD47" box="[1029,1213,655,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1876-01-30">30 January 1876</date>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FB42FD79FF53FD20" author="Dekker, R. W. R. J. &amp; Quaisser, C." pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref14033" refString="Dekker, R. W. R. J. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2006) Type-specimens of birds in the National Museum of Natural History, Leiden. Part 3. Passerines: Pachycephalidae - Corvidae (Peters's sequence). NNM Technical Bulletin, 9, 1 - 77." type="journal article" year="2006">Dekker &amp; Quaisser 2006</bibRefCitation>
). This was not listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6322FFD8FE67FD45FD25FD23" author="Salvadori, T." box="[482,674,691,717]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, but as Salvadori in his original description wrote that he had examined several specimens collected by Beccari and Bruijn in the Arfak mountains, also this RMNH specimen must be considered part of the 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6322FFD8FE17FD0DFE45FCFB" box="[402,450,763,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
